        <mxCell id="wb" parent="1" style="text;html=0;strokeColor=none;fillColor=none;align=left;verticalAlign=top;fontSize=11;fontColor=#7A6000;spacingLeft=4;spacingTop=4;whiteSpace=wrap;" value="Reasoning model capabilities are only valuable when the task actually requires them. For tasks that do not require multi-step reasoning, self-verification, or multi-constraint satisfaction, the extended compute is pure waste.  The corollary is equally important: using a standard model for a genuinely complex reasoning task produces worse outputs — not marginally worse, but worse in ways that affect decisions and downstream systems.  The discipline is the taxonomy, not the preference." vertex="1">
